title: Monday's roundup | Kellam's Park in 7th place at state golf tourney
text:
GOLF Group 6A state championships
Kellam's Leonard Park led the South Hampton Roads field in seventh place, three shots behind the leader, after the first round Monday at Magnolia Green Golf Course in Moseley.
Kellam is out of the four team competitors. Chantilly leads the field with 299, 27 strokes ahead of the Knights.
Riverbend's Jake Miles shot a 1-under 71 for first place. Landstown's Raphael Olfato carded a 75 for eighth place.
____
Group 5A state championships
Hickory's Patrick Gareiss was in seventh after a 5-over 77 heading into today's final round at Magnolia Green Golf Course.
No South Hampton Roads teams are vying for the team title. Deep Run leads Thomas Jefferson, Mills Godwin and North Stafford.
Jefferson's Nathan Chuwait shot a 2-under 70 to lead the field.
____
Group 4A state championships
Great Bridge's Carter Old and EJ Whiten shot an 81 and 82, respectively, in the first round at Glenrochie Golf Course in Abingdon.
Old was tied for 12th and Whiten was tied for 16th as the Wildcats were third out of four teams in the team competition.
Loudoun Valley (303) was 35 strokes ahead of Great Bridge. Loudoun Valley's Brandon Weaver led the field after shooting a 2-under 70.
____
BOYS SOCCER
Cape Henry 2, Benedictine 2
Grant Shepherd scored the equalizer midway through the second half, Wladimir Gassant scored with two minutes left in overtime but Benedictine knotted it in the extra period's final seconds.
____
GIRLS VOLLEYBALL
Granby 3, Salem 2
Miranda Cooksey tallied 21 kills and the No. 9 Comets (17-4) edged the SunDevils 25-17, 25-21, 20-25, 20-25, 15-8.
Granby's Maddy McCormick had 33 assists and four blocks.
____
Oscar Smith 3, King's Fork 1
Arianna Mackey, Hannah Trotman and Jadazia Stanifer combined for 21 kills as the Tigers won 25-19, 25-22, 18-25, 25-19.
